MakerJs.IModel.description:
A model is a composite object which may contain an array of paths, or an array of models recursively.

Example:
```
var m = { 
   paths: { 
     "line1": { type: 'line', origin: [0, 0], end: [1, 1] }, 
     "line2": { type: 'line', origin: [0, 0], end: [-1, -1] } 
   } 
};
```

